    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.30/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-03T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 1, 12 noon, and December 2, 12 noon.<note n="1" xml:id="d556fn1"
                        >Latter not printed.</note> Navy Department ready to comply with request of
                    Brazilian Government us to five naval officers; names will be cabled as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to present cordial invitation to Brazilian Government to send
                    squadron of destroyers to join American naval forces now operating against the
                    enemy. Navy Department has communicated with Admiral <persName corresp="#p_SWS1"
                        >Sims</persName> in London in regard to disposal <pb facs="0552" n="380"
                        xml:id="pg_380"/> of Brazilian squadron, if invitation is accepted. You will
                    be informed immediately upon receipt of his reply. Probable disposition southern
                    waters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
